Joe Batt’s Arm, Fogo Island, Newfoundland. Fogo Island sits in the heart of Iceberg Alley and when a season comes along with plenty of Icebergs you can see them close enough to smack you in the face or just stand by and watch the parade make its way through the alley. A flat calm morning yesterday created the first two views in the early morning light. If you like minimalist images Fogo Island has many views to stimulate your imagination. For those of you wondering, the annual spring parade of icebergs from West Greenland takes 1-3 years to arrive here and the 10,000 year old ice is captivating to see and tastes great. As always feel free to visit our profile to see more.

For Newfoundlanders who grew up in similar type surrounding and visit here it really is a jolt to the memory 
That said the presence of the newer Squish Studio fits in nicely. As always feel free to visit our profile to see more.
